270 South Street, at the N.W. corner of Jefferson Street, showing the Plymouth Hotel. Also shown, is Jefferson Street, west side, north from South Street.

March 31, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

South Street, north side, east from Jefferson, to and including Clinton Streets, showing the Freeborn Buildings (foreground) occupied by the Fidelity Warehouse Co. These buildings, Nos. 271-274, are at the N.E. corner. They were erected in 1859. Adjoining same, are the S. W. Driggs storehouse, which bear Nos. 275-280.

March 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
